The '''''Encyclopædia Universalis''''' is a [[French language|French-language]] general [[encyclopedia]] published by [[Encyclopædia Britannica, Inc.]], a privately held company. The articles of the ''Encyclopædia Universalis'' are aimed at educated adult readers, and written by a staff of full-time editors and expert contributors. It is widely considered to be the most scholarly of French-language encyclopedias.{{Citation needed|date=November 2007}}

