[[File:Ton Kootpenning.jpg|thumb|The Ton Kootpenning]]
'''Ton Koot''' (1907–1986) was secretary of the Amsterdam [[Rijksmuseum]]. He was vice-president of the Amsterdam Tourist Office and was a prolific author of books promoting the history and attractions of the city.<ref>[https://archief.amsterdam/inventarissen/overzicht/10112.nl.html 10112: Collectie Ton Koot.] Gemeente Amsterdam Stadsarchief. Retrieved 7 August 2017.</ref> The Ton Kootpenning has been awarded since 1972 for services to the preservation of heritage and commitment to monument protection.<ref>[https://erfgoedstem.nl/ton-kootpenning-voor-prof-dr-vincent-van-rossem/ Ton Kootpenning voor Prof. Dr. Vincent van Rossem.] De Erfgoedstem, 1 February 2013. Retrieved 7 August 2017.</ref>

